<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-196-135 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 575 174</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  March 25 1991 n634 p57(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Taking a peek at the 'Body Electric'.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wirbel, Loring.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>VPL Research Inc's Body Electric virtual programming language maychange the way people program in real-time environments.andP;  VPL,which stands for visual programming language, began programmingtwo-dimensional icons in 1984 and has moved to three-dimensionalpolygon structures.andP;  The company produces Swivel, a specialMacintosh front-end development program for defining the shapesand dynamical constraints of objects that exist in an artificialworld.andP;  Swivel 3D is a graphical manipulation tool can be used forgeneral-purpose design, RB2 Swivel is designed for developingvirtual reality programs.andP;  The company is developing methods forlinking human sensors to object interaction; visual sensorinformation is currently the most developed, sound is quicklyfollowing.andP;  VPL uses EyePhone goggles and a DataGlove to simulatethree-dimensional realities.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   VPL Research Inc. (Research).andO;Topic:     Research and DevelopmentVirtual RealityThree-Dimensional GraphicsHuman FactorsSimulationReal-Time SystemsProgram Development TechniquesProgramming.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>